WEBVTT

00:00.243 --> 00:04.565
Try these tips to take your act out of your living room and in front of a live audience.

00:04.943 --> 00:08.458
Step 1: Write original material for your routine.

00:08.692 --> 00:11.924
Whenever inspiration strikes, write it down immediately.

00:12.284 --> 00:17.619
Step 2: Develop your act by rehearsing your material and finding an original voice.

00:17.722 --> 00:21.732
Study successful comedians for tips on delivery, timing, and attitude.

00:21.975 --> 00:24.438
Step 3: Get on stage often.

00:24.567 --> 00:28.550
It's critical for a stand-up to practice before an audience as much as possible.

00:28.877 --> 00:31.345
Step 4: Read the audience.

00:31.577 --> 00:33.819
If you're not getting laughs, shift gears.

00:33.947 --> 00:35.861
Be prepared to stray from your material...

00:35.934 --> 00:41.317
...and improvise to mine comedy from spontaneous situations, and defuse hecklers.

00:41.845 --> 00:46.346
Step 5: Record your set when you have it down, and make a DVD.

00:46.547 --> 00:51.474
Professional comics send these to comedy clubs around the country as a way to audition for a booking.

00:51.826 --> 00:55.701
Step 6: Show respect to fellow comedians and club owners.

00:55.917 --> 00:59.850
Staying in good graces is crucial if you want to continue to work.

00:59.965 --> 01:04.125
Step 7: Have one or more seasoned comics as a mentor.

01:04.260 --> 01:08.845
Most professional comics learned a lot about the business from hanging out with older comics,...

01:08.924 --> 01:10.629
...and listening to their words of wisdom.

